content:
OmniScripts Time Element

Enable users to select from a list of times by adding the Time element to your OmniScript. Format the display and set the time intervals.

Drag a Time element from the Build panel onto the canvas.
In the Properties panel, give the element a name in the Name field.
In Field Label, enter a label visible to the user.
In Minimum Time, enter the earliest time the user can select, such as 12:00 am.
The format entered must be the same as in the Time Format field.

In Maximum Time, enter the latest time the user can select, such as 08:00 pm.
The format entered must be the same as in the Time Format field.

In Time Format, enter the format to display the time, such as hh:mm a, which is the default.
Enter h or hh for hour, m or mm for minute, s or ss for seconds, and a for am/pm.

In Time Interval, enter the intervals within an hour the user can select from the time dropdown. For example, enter 15 for 15 minute periods within the hour such as 12:00, 12:15, 12:30, 12:45, and so on.
(Optional) In the Advanced Options section, update values for Data Type, Model Time Format, or other properties.

Time Properties are configurable from the Properties panel when you select a Time element.
title: Configuring OmniScripts Time Element
